def count_characters(input_string):
    char_count = {}
    for char in input_string:
        char_count[char] = char_count.get(char, 0) + 1

    for char, count in char_count.items():
        print(f"{char} = {count:02}")

user_input = input("Input: Please enter a string\n")
count_characters(user_input)

After running this , we input the string "Mississippi," 
it will display the character counts as follows: 

Input: Please enter a string
Mississippi
i = 04
s = 04
p = 02
m = 01
